quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,106,"And [it is] a Qur’ān which We have separated [by intervals] that you might recite it to the people over a prolonged period. And We have sent it down progressively."
  17,107,"Say, ",footnotes:1:i.e., the righteous among the People of the Scriptures who recognize the truth contained in the Qur’ān.
  17,108,"And they say, "
  18,73,"[Moses] said, "
  18,74,"So they set out, until when they met a boy, he [i.e., al-Khiḍr] killed him. [Moses] said, "
  18,75,"[Al-Khiḍr] said, "
  19,34,"That is Jesus, the son of Mary - the word of truth about which they are in dispute."
  19,35,"It is not [befitting] for Allāh to take a son; exalted is He!{1} When He decrees an affair, He only says to it, ",footnotes:1:i.e., far removed is He from any such need.
  19,36,"[Jesus said], "
  20,16,"So do not let one avert you from it{1} who does not believe in it and follows his desire, for you [then] would perish.",footnotes:1:From preparation for the Hour or for the Hereafter.
  20,17,"And what is that in your right hand, O Moses?"
  20,18,"He said, "